title: Learning Outcomes
body:
• Identify the internal and accessory structures of the eye & explain their functions.
  • Trace the structures through which light passes as it travels from the cornea to the retina.

title: Learning Outcomes
body:
• Identify the parts of the external, middle & inner ear and describe their functions.
  • Trace the pathways of sound vibrations from the tympanic membrane to the hearing receptors.

title: Component title
body:
Identify the following structures in the physical ear model:

  1. Auricle (pinna) 
  2. External acoustic meatus
  3. Tympanic membrane (ear drum)
instruction: Click on the button below once you are done with the physical model.

title: Middle ear
body:
Identify the following structures on the ear models:

  1. Tympanic cavity
  2. Auditory ossicles
    1. Malleus
    2. Incus
    3. Stapes
  3. Oval window

_items.text: I can identify all 5 structures in the middle ear.
I can identify 3 or 4 structures in the middle ear.
I can identify 0 to 2 structures in the middle ear.

title: Eustachian tube
instruction: Identify the Eustachian tube (auditory tube) in the physical model.

title: Vestibulocochlear nerve
body:
Identify the following structures in the physical ear model:

  1. Vestibular branch
  2. Cochlear branch

title: Inner ear
body:
Identify the following structures in the physical ear model:

  1. Semicircular canals
  2. Vestibule
    1. Utricle
    2. Saccule
  3. Cochlea

_items.text: I can identify all 4 structures in the inner ear.
I can identify 2 to 3 structures in the inner ear.
